mall and have a husband in Canada.

07:50.747 --> 07:53.140
I told him he's crazy.
Because he's crazy, right?

07:53.156 --> 07:55.581
I mean, how crazy is that?

07:55.908 --> 07:57.913
Are you asking me
if I'm married?

07:57.928 --> 07:59.192
Well, you can ask me.

07:59.207 --> 08:01.330
Nope, I'm not married.
Your turn.

08:01.345 --> 08:03.451
What happened to
respecting my privacy?

08:03.467 --> 08:06.122
Look, just say, "No,
I'm not married."

08:06.138 --> 08:07.953
Ted, I don't understand
why you can't--

08:07.967 --> 08:10.513
Just say, "No,
I'm not married."

08:10.527 --> 08:12.162
I can't.

08:12.318 --> 08:14.182
Marshall's right.

08:16.276 --> 08:18.980
I was young and I got married.

08:18.996 --> 08:20.962
It was a mistake and
he moved away, but...

08:20.976 --> 08:23.801
yeah. I'm married.

08:33.086 --> 08:34.751
You have a husband?

08:34.768 --> 08:36.692
I was young and stupid

08:36.707 --> 08:39.970
and we got married at a mall
and we broke up at a mall

08:39.986 --> 08:42.730
and I...
I haven't been to a mall since.

08:42.748 --> 08:44.101
Why didn't you get divorced?

08:44.115 --> 08:46.573
He moved to Hong Kong for
work and I was like...

08:46.586 --> 08:47.991
eh, good enough.

08:48.005 --> 08:50.211
Good enough?
That's not good enough.

08:50.226 --> 08:53.321
You  order pancakes, you get waffles,
that's good enough.

08:53.337 --> 08:56.523
Look, I haven't
seen him in years.

08:56.537 --> 08:59.380
It's just a part of my
life I want to forget.

08:59.808 --> 09:02.682
Just please don't tell
anyone about this.

09:03.735 --> 09:05.392
Okay.

09:08.508 --> 09:10.942
Dude, your hand is monstrous.

09:10.955 --> 09:13.660
